Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{1/2%pack} from your fridge to allow it to come up to room temperature.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the mushrooms are frying, chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once your mushrooms are browned, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @gochujang paste{50%grams}, @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{100%milliliters} for the sauce to combine. Add the @slow cooked British chicken{290%grams} along with the juices from the packet.

Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a fork, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once tender, remove the lid and use two #forks{} to gently break apart the chicken. Stir through the @BBQ sauce{80%grams} and @butter{20%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

> Ensure the chicken is piping hot throughout.

Transfer your gochujang chicken filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Cover with the pastry, pressing it over the side of the dish or just sitting it on top, then trimming off any excess.

Make a small hole in the middle to allow steam to escape.

> Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once it's out of the oven, allow it to stand for ~{2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a medium #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%milliliters} with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Just before serving, toss the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} through the dressing until well coated.

Share the gochujang chicken pie between your plates. Serve with the sesame chips and salad on the side. Enjoy!